  <steps>
    <step num="0">In a small bowl, combine flour, salt, and pepper. </step>
    <step num="1">Rub the flour mixture on the beef, making sure it is covered entirely. </step>
    <step num="2">Heat oil in large skillet. Sear the meat on every side until golden brown. </step>
    <step num="3">Transfer meat into slow cooker. </step>
    <step num="4">Add onion, celery, carrot, garlic, tomatoes, wine, herbs, bay leaf, and salt. </step>
    <step num="5">Cook on low for 8 hours. </step>
    <step num="6">Serve it with your favorite side dish and sprinkle some freshly chopped parsley. </step>
    <step num="7">Enjoy! </step>
  </steps>
